Problem:-Valid Parentheses

Given a string s containing just the characters '(', ')', '{', '}', '[' and ']', determine if the input string is valid.

An input string is valid if:
Open brackets must be closed by the same type of brackets.
Open brackets must be closed in the correct order.
Every close bracket has a corresponding open bracket of the same type.
 
Example 1:
Input: s = "()"
Output: true

Solutions:-

LeetCode 20: Valid Parentheses validates matching brackets with correct order using stack. Classic stack problem.

#Java Implementation (Stack)

class Solution {
    public boolean isValid(String s) {
        Stack<Character> stack = new Stack<>();
        Map<Character, Character> map = new HashMap<>();
        map.put(')', '(');
        map.put('}', '{');
        map.put(']', '[');
        
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            // Closing bracket
            if (map.containsKey(c)) {
                if (stack.isEmpty() || stack.pop() != map.get(c)) {
                    return false;
                }
            }
            // Opening bracket
            else {
                stack.push(c);
            }
        }
        
        return stack.isEmpty();
    }
}

Stack matching: Push opens, pop on matching close.

#Step-by-Step Logic
HashMap: close → expected open
For each char:
Closing bracket: map.containsKey(c)
Stack empty → invalid
Top ≠ expected open → invalid
Else pop ✓
Opening bracket: push(c)
Final: stack.empty() → valid
Trace: "({[]})"

text
'(': push → stack=['(']
'{': push → ['(','{']
'[': push → ['(','{','[']
']': pop '[' ✓ → ['(','{']
'}': pop '{' ✓ → ['(']  
')': pop '(' ✓ → []
Empty ✓ → true

#Thought Process
Stack perfect fit: LIFO matches nested brackets

text
()[]{} → nested structure
Two-pass reverse invalid → stack natural
HashMap efficient: O(1) close→open lookup vs multiple ifs
Single pass: O(n) time, O(n) space

#Alternatives:
Counter fails on order: "([)]" → wrong
Two pointers impossible (random order)

#Edge Cases
Empty: "" → true ✓
Single: "(" → false (leftover)
Odd length: "(()" → false
Wrong order: "([)]" → false
Interleaved: ")(" → false
